# Import Conventions

## Rules

1. **Use path aliases for cross-feature imports**: When importing from different feature areas or directories, always use path aliases instead of relative paths with `../` or `../../../`.

2. **Use relative imports for local files**: When importing from the same folder (`./`) or immediate parent/sibling (`../`), use relative paths to reduce noise.

3. **Decision criteria**:
   -  If the import requires 2+ levels of `../` → Use path aliasY
   -  If the import is within the same feature/module → Use relative path
   -  If the import crosses feature boundaries → Use path alias

## Available Path Aliases

-  `~/*` → `./src/*` (use for components, infrastructure, domain, app, etc.)
-  `@constants/*` → `./constants/*`
-  `@assets/*` → `./assets/*`
-  `@public/*` → `./public/*`

## Examples

### ✅ Good - Using path aliases for cross-feature imports

```typescript
// Importing components from anywhere
import { Header } from '~/components/layouts/Header';
import { Button } from '~/components/ui/Button';

// Importing from src directory (infrastructure, domain, app)
import { CatalogService } from '~/infrastructure/services/catalog.service';
import { CatalogType } from '~/domain/types/catalog.type';
import { useAuth } from '~/app/hooks/useAuth';

// Importing constants
import { API_ENDPOINT } from '@constants/api';
```

### ❌ Bad - Deep relative paths (avoid)

```typescript
// Too many levels - hard to read and maintain
import { Header } from '../../../components/layouts/Header';
import { CatalogService } from '../../infrastructure/services/catalog.service';
import { CatalogType } from '../../../domain/types/catalog.type';
```

### ✅ Good - Relative imports for local files

```typescript
// Same folder
import { Button } from './Button';
import { ButtonProps } from './Button.types';

// Immediate parent or sibling
import { Modal } from '../shared/Modal';
import { useLocalState } from '../hooks/useLocalState';
```

### ❌ Bad - Unnecessary path aliases for local files

```typescript
// Overkill for same-folder imports
import { Button } from '~/components/ui/Button'; // when already in ~/components/ui folder
import { Modal } from '~/components/shared/Modal'; // when already in components folder
```
